#  Playing with window title, making it go
#  to whatever side of the window we want:

Key Left WTSF1234567890 CM WindowStyle TitleAtLeft
Key Right WTSF1234567890 CM WindowStyle TitleAtRight
Key Up WTSF1234567890 CM WindowStyle TitleAtTop
Key Down WTSF1234567890 CM WindowStyle TitleAtBottom

#  Grouping windows and switching between
#  groups and inside them:
#
#  "Group" a grouped window once again
#  to dismiss it.
#
#  One window can belong to several groups.

Key 1 WTSF1234567890 CM4 AddToGroup 1
Key 2 WTSF1234567890 CM4 AddToGroup 2
Key 3 WTSF1234567890 CM4 AddToGroup 3
Key 1 A MCS4 GroupSwitch 1
Key 2 A MCS4 GroupSwitch 2
Key 3 A MCS4 GroupSwitch 3

# move between desktops
Key 1 WTSF1234567890 S4 MoveToDesk 0 0
Key 2 WTSF1234567890 S4 MoveToDesk 0 1
Key 3 WTSF1234567890 S4 MoveToDesk 0 2
Key 4 WTSF1234567890 S4 MoveToDesk 0 3

#  Screenshots and screencasts made easy:
#Key Print A N FvwmDesktopScreenshot
Key Print A N Exec exec xfce4-screenshooter

#  Quake-like fvwm console
Key Q A 4 QLikeFvwmConsole  734 362 80 80

# 2 different ways for fullscreen windows, 2nd one keeps the borders
Key F11 A M Exec exec wmctrl -r :ACTIVE: -b toggle,fullscreen,above
Key F9 A M Fullscreen

#Key (feh) i WTSF1234567890 N Iconify

Mouse 3 R A Menu MainMenu
#Mouse 1 R A WindowList Root NoGeometry
